      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Dev Role\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to take a moment to thank you for your interest in the Senior Dev role at our Austin office and for the time you invested in the interview process. We were impressed by your technical skills and your passion for development.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. This decision was not easy, as we were genuinely impressed by your abilities and potential.\n\nWe understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this decision was not made lightly. We truly appreciate your interest in our company and hope that you will keep an eye on our career page for future opportunities that may be a better fit for your skills and experience.\n\nThank you once again for your time and effort. We wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]",
